# Branding rule

All user-visible nouns for the active vertical live in [`lib/branding.ts`](mdc:lib/branding.ts).
Pull them from there; do not hardcode "Restaurant", "Worker", "Tip", "Roosterwise",
or any other vertical-specific word in component code.

```ts
import { branding } from '@/lib/branding';

// ✅
<h1>{branding.productName} console</h1>
<p>Manage your {branding.payeePlural.toLowerCase()}.</p>
<button>Run {branding.payoutNoun.toLowerCase()}</button>

// ❌
<h1>Roosterwise console</h1>
<p>Manage your workers.</p>
<button>Run tip-out</button>
```

## When you may keep a literal

- Marketing prose blocks (`app/page.tsx` hero, `Module Receipt` feature copy).
  Reskinning a vertical includes rewriting the marketing copy; this is fine.
- SVG monogram letters that follow `branding.productName.charAt(0)`.
- Dev-only values in `e2e-test.js`.

## When you must NOT keep a literal

- Form labels, table headers, page titles, breadcrumbs, button copy.
- Toasts, error messages, success messages.
- Email placeholder values (`branding.merchantSingular.toLowerCase()` works fine).

## Reskinning checklist (one-file change)

When asked to "reskin to <vertical>":

1. Open `lib/branding.ts`.
2. Edit `productName`, `merchantSingular/Plural`, `payeeSingular/Plural`,
   `payoutNoun/Plural`, `funderLabel`, `tagline`, `consoleHeading`,
   `consoleSubheading`.
3. Optional: update the marketing copy on `app/page.tsx`.
4. Stop. Do not edit `lib/types/*`, `lib/hooks/*`, `app/actions/*`, route
   handlers, or Redis keys.
